	Sanaa wins ITF meet  Gurgaon: Third seed Sanaa Bhambri spanked seven seed Sung-Hee Han of Korea in straight sets to clinch the singles title of the ITF women rsquo;s tennis tournament on Saturday. Sanaa saved the best for the final as she notched up a 7-5, 6-1 victory over her Korean opponent to win the final match and pocket $10,000. Sanaa had been in commanding form throughout the tournament, with the only major scare coming from the eighth seeded Parija Maloo, whom she beat 7-5, 3-6, 6-2 in a hard-fought semi-final encounter on Friday.     
